 \mathrm{Si}(\pi)/\pi - 1/2 \approx 
 \frac{\pi}{4} + (-1)^{n-1} \frac{\pi}{2} e_n = \lim_{N\to\infty}S_N f \left( \frac{2\pi n}{2N} \right) \quad \dots \implies 
 (-1)^{n-1} e_n = \frac{n}{\pi} \mathrm{Si}\left( \frac{\pi}{n} \right) - \frac{1}{2} . 
